entries.femaleVariant: Chooms, chooms, listen! What if instead of an arm... we chipped him with iron? Every time he'd have to take a piss, he'd... bwahaha!
Ha! And then he'll start a next-gen Buddhist fellowship of... get this! Full Metal Monks! Bwaha-bwahaha!
Fuck, got a break in!
Help! Let me out of here!
Do not do this! Implantation is against my beliefs! Please... I do not want them!
Heard you call out for help.
Your brother sent me.
You can thank your brother.
Was walking by and caught some lame jokes about metal monks. Thing about Maelstrom – they're never just joking...
entries.maleVariant: Was walking by and caught some lame jokes about metal monks. Thing about Maelstrom – they're never just jokin'...

entries.femaleVariant: Was walking by and caught some lame jokes about metal monks. Thing about Maelstrom – they're never just joking...

entries.femaleVariant: From the bottom of my soul – thank you. I am especially grateful nobody was killed. May you continue on the path of peace.
What compels these monsters is of no consequence. It is not up to us to judge what they deserve.
Thank you for coming to my rescue... but my life is not worth the death of others.
Your brother's waiting for you.
Don't I get a "Thank you?"
I didn't really have a choice.
Your brother's waiting for you. Not far from here.
First, I must catch my breath and then I shall go. It is him who shall need saving now...
You know, if it wasn't for me, you'd be a chrome cripple.
I appreciate your good will, but I cannot be grateful for the loss of human life you have caused.
What was I s'posed to do? Read 'em a sermon? Maelstrom shoots first, then asks questions.
You always have a choice, including not to act at all. That is the most difficult of paths.
I would prefer to lose the only body I have than to live with the thought that someone died on my account.
Leave me. I must catch my breath before I go to my brother. It is him who needs saving now.
Shit, shit, shit! Don't die!
Why the fuck do I always gotta be the lookout? Wonder if this one'll try anything funny...
Please! Dharma has brought me peace. Do not deprive me of it...!
Look who's takin' the righteous path... If you're so afraid of killin', maybe you should've become a monk 'stead of a merc.
Who knew monks were ungrateful little brats? Maybe you should apologize for saving his 'ganic ass, too!
Nail that meatbag to the wall!
Calm down, it's over now. I'm not with them.
So... what are you doing here? What happened?
You stole my fuckin' joke!
One good deed does not justify the suffering you have sewn. You have committed evil in its purest form.
Hehehe, it's like – it's like he's gonna be a Full Metal Monk!
I said no at first, but he looked so desperate... I knew if I didn't do anything, I'd regret it.
Killing isn't the solution to everything.
If you wanna change the world, there's always a price to be paid.
Tired of assholes saying there are good and bad people in this world. There are only good choices and shitty ones.
Must've made a good one, 'cause why else would karma leave all this sweet gear just ripe for the pickin'?
Open your flap again and I'll rip your tongue out.
So this is where they're keeping our fellow brother.
The suffering we commit unto others always finds a way back to us. Always.
Leave me. I must catch my breath before I go to my brother. It is him who needs saving now.
As for these chrome-fucks – you think they got all this gear by sitting around going "Oommm"?
How'd you even get taken by Maelstrom? Most people avoid 'em like the plague.
How did you get taken by Maelstrom?
We are here as strangers. We wander from place to place. When we arrived in Night City, we had no time to identify its dangers.
Don't monks live in monasteries?
It used to be they did not. My brother and I belong to a group that follows the earliest Buddhist teachings.
It is an interesting life. We have met many unusual people.
So I see.
There is no need for sarcasm. We know the world is dangerous.
But if one takes no risks, one will never know what lies beyond their front door. I'm sure you understand.
When I heard you call out, I knew there was no time to lose.
Nah, but the truth's that your brother sent me. He didn't want the same thing to happen to you.
entries.maleVariant: Nah, the truth – your brother sent me. He didn't want the same thing to happen to you.

entries.femaleVariant: But the truth's that I was sent by your brother.
entries.maleVariant: But the truth is that I was sent by your brother.

entries.femaleVariant: Glad I got here in time. Are you OK? Did they do anything to you?
First, I wanna make sure you're OK.
If they had enough to spare on monks, then surely they don't need all of it...
I like where you're going with this.
I was lucky. They could not decide which implant would be... funnier.
One... one of them wanted to remove my jaw. The thought itself gives me shivers...
Thankfully, they did not get the chance. To what do I owe this... intervention of yours?
Cyberpsychos, the lot of 'em...
Um... yeah, sure.
Hmph, I liked your brother more.
It's OK, you're safe.
Your brother's waiting.
What was I supposed to do?
